Lamu girl - Kenya
A favourite destination for globetrotters in the 1970s, LAMU quickly became a haunting ground for the more overt members of the jet set. The archipelago, stuck between Somalia avec an abandoned part of Kenya, is formed by three axes: the town of Lamu, the neighbouring village of Shela, whose population is being ousted by rich European owners, and on the other side, the island on Manda, where the French citizen was kidnapped. Easy-going lifestyle, a UNESCO classified town, no cars, thousands of donkeys in the streets, a tolerant Islam, behind these clichés Lamu is awakening with a hangover…

